  "text": "A large body of work on side-channel attacks exists, exposing user data via readings of sensors on phones and wearable devices. For instance, work exists on revealing user data, e.g. PIN or graphical passwords through reading of accelerometer data [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Spreitzer et al. [CITATION_4] provide a comprehensive survey and systematic analysis of this line of work. It clearly supports our claim that our work is the first active acoustic side-channel attack.",
